1.) I might be an auntie tonight or tomorrow!! 2.) My Avon manager is a cunt. 3.) I won $30 on a $1 scratchie ticket today. =) 4.) Computer got a virus...had to redo the comp. Lost all my files...all my wedding shit. Gone. A new book I started working on, gone. It was pretty shitty. Other news? For weeks Steve has been telling me that we can afford a PS2. I told him, no for weeks. Well, today we decided yea, we suppose we can afford one. So we got to Wal*Mart all happy and whatnot. We get there and ask where they are...there are none. PS2's are being redesigned and will be released the day after Thanksgiving, and if we want one, be there by 5:30 am. Wal*Mart, Shopko, target, their online stores...no one has em. So Steve told me he'd be at Wal*Mart at 5 am to get me one. Sweet, eh? So, once I have it, The only way someone will get a hold of me is when i beat the new Ratchet and Clank game...or come to my house. =) I'm so lame it hurts.

Something creepy happened tonight. Steve and I went over to visit Tracy. We got home around 9ish tonight. Well, I get out of the car, walk to the screen door and try to open it. Won't open. It's locked. I looked at Steve and told him it was locked. We tried the other screen door...locked. We went around to the back door...locked. The strange thing. The only way to lock the screen door, is from the inside. And I never lock the back doors, in case we get locked out/forget the keys. We managed to get the screen door open. We come inside, nothing has been moved or anything. So I call Jer and ask if it's possible that maybe the lock could fall on the screen door. He says no. Justin case we locked the screen and tried closing the door, wouldnt work. It has to be locked from the inside! So yeah. As far as we know, nothing was touched. But I'm freaked out right now. I dont like the fact that the someone was in here besides Steve and I. And this happens the one time we leave the front gate to the house open. Fuck this. Fuck this house. Fuck this city. And most of all Fuck New Mexico. I can't wait to come home.
Going to Mexico this week.When i come back, I wont be afraid to smile...

Holy fuck. 

My real dad called me. This is the first time we've ever spoken. It was awesome. He told me he loved me and wants a relationship with me. I think i'm going to cry.

Today kinda sucked. At around 4:30 Steve left to go help Jer with something. A few minutes after he took off, the power went out, and so did the phone. Well it was still well over 100 degrees and no power=no swamp cooler. I sat around sweating my ass off for an hour and a half. I found the keys to our other car *no plates, insurance nothing* and drove it to Tracey and Jer's, hoping they had air conditioning. 


Well, We're now back home, with air. Yay! As we pulled in, there were two HUGE trantulas walking around by theporch steps. 

I fucking hate spiders.

Ciggerettes, Fruit Punch and Doritos. My what an interesting day.

David called me yesterday. That made me so happy! I miss my Aussie!

.:blows kisses:.

Now? Off to molest Steve.

Just finished taking the cornrows and briads out of my hair. It feels so much better!

The fireworks were pretty nifty...except for the fact that they last an hour and a half. 

Well a couple days ago i retired all of my jelly bracelets. 2 lbs! Yea. I couldnt believe it. I also took out my eyebrow rings, since they were beginning to bother me. The next thing to go? Prolly my earrings.

Alright. Eariler tonight Tracy cam by and picked me up because I needed to get dog food for my grandmas three dogs. Well when the door opened the bolted and took off. We figured they'd stay in the yard but locked the gate just in case. Well a little while later we get home and only two dogs are in the yard. My grandmas favorite one, Geno, not being one of them. I was freaking out. None of us really care for this dog since he shits everywhere and pisses where he pleases. We figured that Grandma would think we did something to him out of spite. Tracy and I searched for almost 2 hours, then had Jer and Steve look for him. No luck. I was praying *litterally* that Geno was alright and prayed for his safe return. 

Well I finally laid down, teling myself that tomorrow i would get up and start searching again. I watched Daria and was close to falling asleep. Then i got this weird feeling. Something in me told me to get up and go look outside. Knowing that i wasnt going to fall asleep until i did it, i got up, unlocked the doors and went onto the porch. I looked out the window and saw nothing. Bummed i turned around to go back inside when i heard dog tags jingling. I looked at susie and lady bird *my grams other 2 dogs* and noticed that neither of them had moved, nor do they have tags. I looked back out the window and saw Geno walking up the stairs. 

I let him in and hugged the hell out of him. I was so excited. But yeah. The moral of this story? Trust your gut instincts, praying works...and dont let the dogs outside. 

Goodnight.

Room 8 
Separate But Equal


A man arrives at the gates of heaven.

St. Peter asks, "Religion?" 

The man says, "Methodist." 

St. Peter looks down his list, and says, 
"Go to room 24, but be very quiet as you pass room 8." 

Another man arrives at the gates of heaven. 
"Religion?" "Baptist." "Go to room 18, but be very quiet as you pass room 8." 

A third man arrives at the gates. 
"Religion?" "Jewish." "Go to room 11, but be very quiet as you pass room 8." 

The man says, "I can understand there being different rooms for different religions, 
but why must I be quiet when I pass room 8?" 

St. Peter tells him, "Well the Catholics are in room 8 
and they think they're the only ones here."

I got to see Ben Erdman last night. It made me so happy. 

Well, tomorrow we're leaving, thats if everything goes as planned. We'll be staying the night in south eastern WI. Steve is going to visit family and i'll hopefully be visiting a good friend of mine. 

I got a new dog. A purebred Chihuahua with papers. Hes fucking adorable. We named him Spike. ;) 
But yea, Spike is pawing at my leg so i'm off to walk him. Bye everyone. See you in August.

I'm feeling better. Fever's gone, but the coughing hasnt calmed down all that much. 

Sleep last night..barley. I tossed and turned and hacked up  a lung. When sleep is painful, you know your sick. 

Steve called me at 8 am. I was at the end of a coughing fit, so i answered my phone. He sounded all surprised. He's like "I was calling to just leave a messege, I didnt think youd be awake." Surprise, I was. =D 

Mum called me at 10. She's gotta bring Heather to the dr.'s. She's really sick too. 

But hey, on a good note:: I haven't had a cigg in 3 days.
